    "Notes": "Recieved email on support from Carol for having system boot delay issue and application not responding issue. Upon investigation, Event Viewer logs revealed multiple <strong data-start=\"239\" data-end=\"274\">DistributedCOM (Event ID 10010)</strong> errors caused by Windows components (<code data-start=\"312\" data-end=\"349\">Microsoft.WindowsCommunicationsApps</code>) failing to register with DCOM within the required timeout, contributing to extremely slow startup performance and delayed application response. Logged into the system via ScreenConnect and navigated to <code data-start=\"553\" data-end=\"596\">HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Ole</code>, where the <code data-start=\"608\" data-end=\"620\">EnableDCOM</code> registry value was set to <strong data-start=\"647\" data-end=\"654\">&ldquo;Y&rdquo;</strong>. Updated this value to <strong data-start=\"678\" data-end=\"685\">&ldquo;N&rdquo;</strong> to disable unnecessary DCOM activation retries. Additionally, ran <strong data-start=\"752\" data-end=\"770\"><code data-start=\"754\" data-end=\"768\">sfc /scannow</code></strong> and <strong data-start=\"775\" data-end=\"823\"><code data-start=\"777\" data-end=\"821\">dism /online /cleanup-image /restorehealth</code></strong> to repair any corrupted or missing system files. Currently SFC scan is running.",
